But always they ſet their Snares by Night (I mean) by dark,
               Pro. 1.11. they hope no Body ſees them;
Eccleſ 5.8. but he that is higher than the higheſt regardeth, and there are higher than they.

No wonder therefore, that Cardinal Hoſius, the Pope's Legate, land Preſident of the ſaid Council of Trent, anſwered with as much Impiety as Scurrility to that Objection (namely that King David, being no Biſhop, yet had written the Book of Pſalms) anſwered—Quid ni ſcriberet? Huſius l. 2. contra Johan. Brentium. Scribimus indocti doctique Poemata paſſim; Why ſhould he not write? (quoting a Verſe out of Horace:)
The learned Poets, Songs indite;
Th'unlearned too, do Ballads write.

